⭐️⭐️
@@ @@
[[size 150%]]**Ublin House (Dublin/Lublin)**[[/size]] [[footnote]] Is this a digital review? How the FUCK is it here? //— Seth// [[/footnote]]^^,@< >@^^[[footnote]] The Library is just sort of like that, Seth. You'll get used to it. //— Midnight// [[/footnote]]

One of the worst drinking experiences I've ever had, and I've done the full Eurtecian Underbelly Crawl. [[footnote]] Immediate red flag. Only the most pretentious wankers subject themselves to this and then //brag// about it like it's an achievement rather than a waste of time. //— Morríghan// [[/footnote]]

Firstly, getting //to// the actual place is a bother. While I understand the concern surrounding the Veil and such, you could at the very least serve to put the Lublin entrance somewhere that isn't in full view of an entire street! [[footnote]] When did we start counting alleyways as streets? //— Midnight// [[/footnote]]^^,@< >@^^[[footnote]] To be fair to this person, it's really close to the end of said alley. //— Seth// [[/footnote]] The Dublin entrance is indoors, at the very least, in a little place that the establishment's staff operate.

Now, to actually speak on the place itself, my dearest God, it was horrid. The staff were polite, and clearly the young man who was serving the bar which I elected to drink at was new to the whole bartending affair, but the service itself was //horrible.//[[footnote]] Service is never //that// bad, unless there's some sort of health crisis going on or it's a holiday. When did this guy even visit? //— Seth// [[/footnote]]^^,@< >@^^[[footnote]] If the date at the bottom is to be believed, this dumbass showed up on Saint Patrick's weekend two years ago and has the balls to complain about it. //— Morríghan// [[/footnote]] It took a solid ten minutes of me sitting at the bar to even be noticed, and another ten before I had a drink in front of me. To add to that, this place's actual selection of drink is //extremely// narrow. If you aren't a fan of either of its sponserships' products, your options are Bulmers, Pilsner of some sort or some kind of alchemical concoction that tastes vaguely like vodka.[[footnote]] That'd be the Fae-style poitín. I have a sneaking suspicion this guy checked into a hospital for liver failure a few hours after he wrote this, if it tastes like vodka you haven't diluted it well enough. //— Morríghan// [[/footnote]] Additionally, the snack choices were abysmal. Crisps, those tiny little bangers on toothpicks,[[footnote]] Fucking //bangers.// Just call them sausages, fuck me. //— Morríghan// [[/footnote]] next to nothing else. Not even a menu for burgers or something.

Onto the actual quality of my time there, that too was horrible. Maybe it was just the day that was in it, but the place was packed from wall to wall. This is probably a very pedantic reason to mark it down, but I do prefer being able to move when I'm at a bar, especially in the case of bathroom accessibility. Similarly, I will say, while not physically impair, the establishment's bathroom facilities are incredibly accessible, for the able-bodied and disabled, be they dry or drunk. Maybe I'll visit with my wheelchair-bound friend sometime, and see if company makes the experience better.

One more thing I did quite like was the bar's general ambience. There were several bands playing [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=f2MYTBYFXRI Irish and] [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Sj5pMfRcfkE Polish music], traditional from both sides, if memory serves. Not many people were drinking out there and listening, only a few of the bars have outdoor seats and even then there aren't many for those that do. However, it was quite nice, sitting out there and singing along to the Rose of Tralee with an elderly Sidhe man.[[footnote]] Ah, the Rose of Tralee... A lovely song. I sometimes wonder if I would've enjoyed it in my previous lives. //[[[marw-el-reencarnado|~"The Library Cat"]]]//[[/footnote]]^^,@< >@^^[[footnote]] A rare Marw appearance. It's been a while, how've you been? //— Midnight// [[/footnote]]

Overall, my actual experience inside the establishment I chose to drink at during my time at Ublin House was rather poor, sadly. The sheer density of people, combined with the waiting time to get served and the noticeable lack of enough drinks from the taps was all enough to weigh my opinion of the place down. I will, however, keep my review at two stars. I feel the place was lovely, in spite of all this, and had I come by some other time I likely would have had a much better experience. Alas, for now, it remains as such.

//Antoni Nowak//[[footnote]] Any relation to [[[and-every-time-we-meet-again-hub|one Damien Nowak]]]? //— Midnight// [[/footnote]]^^,@< >@^^[[footnote]] According to his profile, he's not from Warsaw, let alone anywhere close to his family. Same name as [[[scp-pl-399|his father]]], but I'd say there's next to no chance that they're related in any meaningful way. //— Morríghan// [[/footnote]]
//Wind Dew Travel Agency Food and Drink Locale Review Agent//
//18/03/2007//

